20/06/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- In a speech Sunday (19 June), Serbian Interior Minister Dragan Jocic reiterated that fighting organised and financial crime, corruption and crimes related to the conflicts in the former Yugoslavia remain police priorities.
He also stressed that public confidence in the police, as an institution guaranteeing public order and security, is on the rise.
Jocic added that reform in the police sector is continuing with support from the international community and EU institutions.
(Politika - 20/06/05;
Beta - 19/06/05)
